  feat: web storefront, anon auth/RLS, collection UI, skeleton sizing

  ## Web platform (new)
  - WebNav: sticky nav bar with search, user avatar dropdown, cart
  badge
  - SellerSidebar: collapsible collection filter panel for storefront
  views
  - StorefrontCatalog: browsable card grid with collection filtering
  - CartPanel: slide-in cart drawer with quantity/price editing
  - WebCartPage, WebOffersPage, WebTransactionsPage,
  WebTransactionDetailPage: full web page layouts
  - BrowserStorefront: root-level /:username clean URL route
  - AuthModal: sign-in / sign-up modal overlay for unauthenticated web
  visitors
  - NavSearchDropdown: real-time user/card search results dropdown
  - LandingPage: updated with CTA, suggested sellers, hero sections
  - Web-specific UI overrides: Badge, BorderLabel, SearchBar,
  Background
  - Web store layer: client.web.ts, useCartStore.web.ts,
  useCartPanelStore
  - app layout: _layout.web.tsx, _providers.web.tsx (anon auto-sign-in,
   web routing)
  - lib/stubs: react-native-skia and react-native-worklets stubs for
  web bundling

  ## Supabase / security
  - Migration: grant SELECT on user_profile + collection_stats to anon
  role
  - Migration: tighten storefront RLS to authenticated-only (anon JWT
  still allowed)
  - Migration: enable RLS on user_profile and demo_user_map with
  public-read policies
  - Migration: pg_cron job to purge expired anonymous users (daily
  03:00 UTC)
  - Migration: pg_cron job to clean up stale notifications
  - Edge function: cleanup-anon-users (invoked by cron)
  - image-proxy: updated CORS / auth handling

  ## Collection UI
  - Group CollectionInfo + items FlatList in a rounded-top card
